data.current_description:
This operation takes the origin domains and returns a JSON object containing the corresponding origin keys for the domains. 
> If you're still using origin key for your Web Drop-in or Components integration, we recommend [switching to client key](https://docs.adyen.com/development-resources/client-side-authentication/migrate-from-origin-key-to-client-key). This allows you to use a single key for all origins, add or remove origins without generating a new key, and detect the card type from the number entered in your payment form.
data.summary_suggestion: Generate origin keys for domain authentication
data.description_suggestion: Generates origin keys for specified origin domains to enable client-side authentication in Web Drop-in or Components integrations. Accepts a list of origin domains and returns a JSON object mapping each domain to its corresponding origin key. Each origin key is domain-specific and required for secure client-side payment form initialization. Note: This endpoint is maintained for backward compatibility; Adyen recommends migrating to client keys for improved flexibility and single-key management across multiple origins.
